  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison arrived in New York in a northeasterly rainstorm and visited Mrs. Sarah S. Savin. He next went to Philadelphia and stayed with Alfred H. Love. He spoke to a large audience in Concert Hall. Richard Purvis has become hostile to Garrison. Kind and sweet Lucretia Mott came to Garrison&apos;s lecture. Garrison writes: &quot;I also had on the platform Rachel Moore, the noted female preacher, who dined with me at Alfred&apos;s.&quot; The weather was cold and clear.</subfield>
